"Thus having pass'd the night in fruitless pain, I to my longing friends return again— Amaz'd the' augmented number to behold, Of men and matrons mix'd, of young and old— A wretched exil'd crew together brought, ‘With arms appointed, and with treasure fraught, Resolv'd, and willing, under my command, To runall hazards both of sea and land. The Morn began, from Ida, to display Her rosy cheeks ; and Phosphor led the day : Before the gates the Grecians took their post, And all pretence of late relief was lost. I yield to Fate, unwillingly retire, And, loaded, up the hill convey my sire."